# Close Sprint (Project Overlay)

The full skill — bidirectional outflow to product AND engineering shores, hypothesis decision, sprint-file deletion — is in the `praxis` plugin's `close-sprint` skill. Read it first.

## Project-specific paths

- Sprint file: `{{paths.sprints}}/SPRINT.<ID>-<slug>.md` (delete at close)
- Product-side updates:
  - The relevant wave at `{{paths.waves}}/wave-NNN-<slug>/`
  - Dashboard at `{{paths.product_dashboard}}`
- Engineering-side updates:
  - The capability record(s) at `{{paths.architecture}}/<capability>/` rewritten to current-state (the validated educated theory becomes truth), and the system overview at `{{paths.architecture}}/README.md` if cross-capability topology/posture changed
  - New or amended ADRs at `{{paths.architecture}}/<capability>/adr/` (or `{{paths.adr}}/` for cross-capability)
  - Capability layout updates in the source tree
  - `{{paths.engineering}}/handbook.md` if a new convention emerged
- TEACH (when user-observable behavior changed):
  - Refresh the capability guide at `{{paths.guides}}/<capability>/` and any journey tutorial at `{{paths.guides}}/tutorials/` via `.github/skills/author-user-docs/SKILL.md`

## Project-specific gates

- Owned by the product manager (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product_manager}}.agent.md`).
- Both shores **must** be updated before the sprint file is deleted. A one-sided close is not a close.
- Hypothesis card outcome (continue / pivot / stop) is recorded in the wave README's progress log, not the dashboard.

## Quality gates before close

The sprint cannot close until: `{{quality_gates.lint}}`, `{{quality_gates.format}}`, `{{quality_gates.type_check}}`, and `{{quality_gates.test}}` all pass.
